# PR Task Item Relationship — Implementation Plan (Revised)

## Background & Clarification

> **One PR task = one or more dedicated APP items.**
> The `tasks_tbl` must produce **one row per assignment**, not one row per item.
> A junction table (`task_items_tbl`) bridges the single task to its multiple `app_items`.

---

## MySQL Queries to Execute in MySQL Workbench

Run **in order** before any PHP changes.

```sql
-- 1. Rename tracking column: NULL = unassigned, user_id value = assigned to that user
ALTER TABLE app_items_tbl
    CHANGE COLUMN app_items_is_assigned
                  app_items_assigned_to BIGINT UNSIGNED NULL DEFAULT NULL;

-- Migrate existing flag data: set item 2 to the user it was assigned to (replace 5 with real user_id)
UPDATE app_items_tbl SET app_items_assigned_to = 5 WHERE app_item_id = 2;

-- 2. Create the junction table: one task → many app items
CREATE TABLE task_items_tbl (
    task_item_id  BIGINT UNSIGNED NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT,
    task_id_fk    BIGINT UNSIGNED NOT NULL,
    app_item_id_fk BIGINT UNSIGNED NOT NULL,
    PRIMARY KEY (task_item_id),
    CONSTRAINT fk_task_items_task
        FOREIGN KEY (task_id_fk) REFERENCES tasks_tbl (task_id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
    CONSTRAINT fk_task_items_app_item
        FOREIGN KEY (app_item_id_fk) REFERENCES app_items_tbl (app_item_id) ON DELETE CASCADE
) ENGINE=InnoDB DEFAULT CHARSET=utf8mb4;
```

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Execute the SQL **before** deploying any PHP changes.

